[30;1m550 | [0m[35m    Roche potential (:math:`\\Phi`, synchronous rotation)[0m
[30;1m551 | [0m[35m    [0m
[30;1m552 | [0m[35m    More massive component (:math:`m_1`) is at (x,y,z) = (0,0,0). Less massive[0m
[30;1m553 | [0m[35m    component (:math:`m_2`) is at (a,0,0).[0m
[30;1m554 | [0m[35m    [0m

[30;1m12 | [0m[35mThe model class of funcFit is OneDFit. The central element of OneDFit[0m
[30;1m13 | [0m[35mis the `evaluate` method, which relates the vector of model parameters values, :math:`P`,[0m
[30;1m14 | [0m[35mto an actual model curve, so that :math:`y_i = f(x_i, P)`, where the :math:`y_i` denote the[0m
[30;1m15 | [0m[35mvalues of the model curve at points :math:`x_i`. An example would be a Gaussian profile.[0m
[30;1m16 | [0m[35mA common problem is to compare the model :math:`f(x_i, P)` with some measurements, :math:`m_i`,[0m
[30;1m17 | [0m[35mwith the goal of finding the set of parameter values, which fits best, i.e., the set, which[0m
[30;1m18 | [0m[35mminimizes some objective function, :math:`g`.[0m
